@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Help - Parent Portal";
}

<style>
    body {
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .help-container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 50px auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #fff;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    h1 {
        text-align: center;
        color: #007bff;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .section {
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .section h2 {
        color: #2248F0;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #007bff;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .section p {
        margin-top: 10px;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    ul {
        margin-top: 15px;
        list-style-type: disc;
        margin-left: 20px;
    }

    .section img {
        max-width: 100%;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        margin-top: 10px;
    }

    .back-button {
        display: block;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 10px 20px;
        background-color: #007bff;
        color: white;
        border-radius: 5px;
        text-align: center;
        text-decoration: none;
        max-width: 150px;
    }

    .back-button:hover {
        background-color: #0056b3;
    }
</style>

<div class="help-container">
    <h1>Parent Portal Help</h1>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            Welcome to the Parent Portal! This page will guide you on how to use the system to track your child's attendance. As a parent, you can view your child's attendance records, see if they have attended school, and receive alerts for any absences.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Tracking Your Child's Attendance</h2>
        <p>
            To view your child's attendance records, follow these steps:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Log in to the Parent Portal using your registered account credentials.</li>
            <li>Once logged in, go to the <strong>"Attendance"</strong> page, which will display the most recent attendance records.</li>
            <li>The attendance records will show the date, whether your child was present or absent, and any comments from the school.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Understanding Attendance Records</h2>
        <p>
            Each attendance record contains the following information:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Date:</strong> The date of the attendance record.</li>
            <li><strong>Status:</strong> The status will show "Present" if your child was in school, or "Absent" if they were not.</li>
            <li><strong>Notes:</strong> If your child was absent, the school may provide additional notes or reasons for the absence.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Alerts for Absences</h2>
        <p>
            You can also set up notifications to receive alerts when your child is marked as absent. To enable alerts:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Go to your profile settings by clicking on your name in the top-right corner of the portal.</li>
            <li>In the settings page, enable the <strong>"Attendance Alerts"</strong> option.</li>
            <li>Once enabled, you will receive notifications via email or SMS whenever your child is absent from school.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Getting Help</h2>
        <p>
            If you encounter any issues or have further questions, feel free to contact our support team by emailing us at <strong>support@schoolname.com</strong> or calling our helpline at <strong>(123) 456-7890</strong>.
        </p>
    </div>

    <a href="@Url.Action("ParentHome", "Home")" class="back-button">Back to Home</a>
</div>
